# Citation Hover Popup Feature

When AI responds in chat, it includes numbered citation references (1, 2, 3...). Currently, clicking these numbers opens a full modal. This change adds a **hover popup** that appears when the user hovers over a citation number, showing a preview of the referenced source content.

## Proposed Changes

### Component: HoverCard UI Component

#### [NEW] [hover-card.tsx](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/frontend/src/components/ui/hover-card.tsx)

Create a Radix UI HoverCard component (shadcn/ui pattern) that shows content on hover. This will be used to wrap citation buttons.

- Install `@radix-ui/react-hover-card` if not present
- Standard shadcn/ui component with `HoverCard`, `HoverCardTrigger`, `HoverCardContent`

---

### Component: Citation Reference System

#### [MODIFY] [source-references.tsx](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/frontend/src/lib/utils/source-references.tsx)

**Changes to [createCompactReferenceLinkComponent](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/frontend/src/lib/utils/source-references.tsx#431-492)** (used in [ChatPanel.tsx](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/frontend/src/components/source/ChatPanel.tsx) for notebook chat):

- Add an optional `contentMap` parameter: `Map<string, string>` mapping `"type:id"` → content text
- Wrap each citation button in a `HoverCard` component
- On hover, display a preview popup showing:
  - Title (from existing `children` text)
  - Content excerpt (first ~300 chars from `contentMap`, truncated with "...")
  - A small footer saying "Click to view full content"
- If no content is available in `contentMap` for a reference, show just the title with "Click to view"

**Changes to [createReferenceLinkComponent](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/frontend/src/lib/utils/source-references.tsx#274-331)** (used in [StreamingResponse.tsx](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/frontend/src/components/search/StreamingResponse.tsx) for search page):

- Same hover popup behavior as above

---

### Component: Content Map Building

#### [MODIFY] [ChatColumn.tsx](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/frontend/src/app/(dashboard)/notebooks/components/ChatColumn.tsx)

- Build a `contentMap: Map<string, string>` alongside the existing `titleMap`
- For sources: map `"source:{id}"` → `source.full_text` (need to fetch via `sourcesApi.get()` or use data already available)
- For notes: map `"note:{id}"` → `note.content`
- Pass `contentMap` down to [ChatPanel](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/frontend/src/components/source/ChatPanel.tsx#61-329)

**Approach**: Since `useSources` returns `SourceListResponse[]` (which doesn't include `full_text`), and `useNotes` returns `NoteResponse[]` (which includes `content`), we need a strategy:

- For **notes**: `content` is already available from `useNotes()` → use directly
- For **sources**: The [SourceListResponse](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/frontend/src/lib/types/api.ts#21-41) doesn't include `full_text`. Instead of fetching every source's full text upfront (expensive), we'll extract unique source IDs from messages, then fetch content lazily using React Query.
- For **insights**: Use `insightsApi.get()` lazily.

**Revised approach — Lazy fetching in the HoverCard component itself**:

Rather than building a full `contentMap` upfront, the hover popup component will fetch content on-demand when the user hovers. This avoids unnecessary API calls and works well with React Query caching.

#### [MODIFY] [ChatPanel.tsx](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/frontend/src/components/source/ChatPanel.tsx)

- Pass `titleMap` to the link component factory (already done)
- No additional changes needed if we use lazy fetching

#### [NEW] [CitationHoverCard.tsx](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/frontend/src/components/common/CitationHoverCard.tsx)

A reusable component that wraps a citation button and adds hover popup behavior:

```tsx
interface CitationHoverCardProps {
  type: ReferenceType   // 'source' | 'note' | 'source_insight'
  id: string
  children: React.ReactNode  // The citation button
}
```

- Uses `HoverCard` from Radix UI
- On hover (open state change), fetches content via:
  - `sourcesApi.get(id)` → `full_text` (for sources)
  - `insightsApi.get(id)` → `content` (for insights)
  - `notesApi.get(id)` → `content` (for notes)
- Uses React Query with `enabled: isOpen` to fetch only on hover
- Shows loading spinner while fetching
- Displays first ~300 characters of content as preview
- Caches results so subsequent hovers are instant

#### [MODIFY] [StreamingResponse.tsx](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/frontend/src/components/search/StreamingResponse.tsx)

- Same pattern: wrap reference links with `CitationHoverCard`

